## RULE 03 — H.264 COPY Path: Always Add Bitstream Filter (LL-006)

Whenever writing `-c:v copy` for H.264 content destined for MPEG-TS output, you MUST
add the `h264_mp4toannexb` bitstream filter. No exceptions.

```python
from exstreamtv.ffmpeg.constants import BSF_H264_ANNEXB

if video_format == VideoFormat.COPY:
    cmd.extend(["-c:v", "copy"])
    cmd.extend(["-bsf:v", BSF_H264_ANNEXB])  # REQUIRED — not optional
```

Without this filter, H.264 from Plex/MP4 (AVCC format) is written into MPEG-TS
without Annex B start codes. The first GOP is corrupted or black on all decoders.

