## RULE 05 — Scheduler Loops: Always Guard Against Empty Output (LL-001)

Any `while` loop that advances a time cursor or schedule index based on items produced
by an inner function MUST have an else branch that advances the index unconditionally
if no items were produced. Without this guard, an empty collection causes an infinite loop.

```python
# WRONG
while current_time < end:
    items = get_items(...)
    if items:
        current_time = items[-1].finish
    # NO ELSE — infinite loop if items is empty

# CORRECT
while current_time < end:
    items = get_items(...)
    if items:
        current_time = items[-1].finish
    else:
        index += 1           # advance unconditionally
        if index >= max_index:
            break
        continue
```

