## RULE 07 — XMLTV Timestamps: Exactly One Format (LL-007)

All XMLTV `<programme start="...">` and `stop` attributes MUST use:
`%Y%m%d%H%M%S +0000`

No dashes, no colons, no "UTC" suffix. The XMLTV spec is strict. Plex silently
rejects any programme element with a non-conforming timestamp.

```python
# WRONG
start_str = dt.strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S UTC")   # XMLTV-invalid
start_str = dt.strftime("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ")       # ISO 8601, not XMLTV

# CORRECT
start_str = dt.strftime("%Y%m%d%H%M%S +0000")
```

