## RULE 08 — EPG Variables: Guard None Before strftime (LL-008)

Any `start_time`, `end_time`, or similar variable used in `.strftime()` during EPG
generation MUST be checked for `None` before use. Position tracking has many branches
that can leave these as `None`.

```python
# WRONG
start_str = start_time.strftime("%Y%m%d%H%M%S +0000")  # AttributeError if None

# CORRECT
if start_time is None:
    logger.warning(f"start_time is None for channel {channel_id}, using now")
    start_time = datetime.now(tz=timezone.utc)
start_str = start_time.strftime("%Y%m%d%H%M%S +0000")
```

