## RULE 09 — Loop Variables: Never Shadow Outer Counters (LL-009)

In EPG generation and schedule engine code, loop variable names `idx`, `i`, `index`
are frequently used as outer counters. Inner loops MUST use distinct names to prevent
shadowing.

```python
# WRONG — shadows outer current_item_index
for idx in range(current_item_index):
    item = schedule_items[idx]

# CORRECT
for _ci in range(current_item_index):
    item = schedule_items[_ci]
```

