## RULE 11 — Async Locks: Never Await Blocking I/O Inside Lock (LL-013)

`async with self._lock:` must contain only fast, non-blocking operations. Never
`await` a subprocess kill, a sleep, a network call, or a DB write inside a lock.
Collect work under the lock, execute it outside.

```python
# WRONG
async with self._lock:
    for item in self._items:
        await self._kill_process(item)  # can block for 5s — deadlocks everything

# CORRECT
to_kill = []
async with self._lock:
    for item in list(self._items):
        if item.needs_kill:
            to_kill.append(item)
            del self._items[item.id]

for item in to_kill:          # outside the lock
    await self._kill_process(item)
```

