## RULE 12 — MPEG-TS Buffer Operations: Align to Sync Byte (LL-014)

Any operation that trims, slices, or seeks in an MPEG-TS byte buffer MUST align the
result to the nearest `0x47` sync byte. Dropping bytes mid-packet produces broken
framing that manifests as freezes and corruption artefacts in Plex.

```python
# WRONG
trimmed = buffer[-max_size:]

# CORRECT
trimmed = buffer[-max_size:]
sync_pos = trimmed.find(0x47)
if sync_pos > 0:
    trimmed = trimmed[sync_pos:]
elif sync_pos == -1:
    trimmed = b""   # no sync — discard entirely
```

